contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:03.303 --> 01:05.436
[SCREAMS]

01:12.979 --> 01:15.112
Really?

01:15.114 --> 01:18.182
You thought this was the
right place to bury a girl?

01:18.184 --> 01:21.796
Where people dig and
plant things for a living?

01:24.286 --> 01:27.353
Go on. Clear off. There's
nothing to see here.

01:27.356 --> 01:28.689
Scarper!

01:28.692 --> 01:30.759
[GASPS]

01:45.079 --> 01:48.180
Go on! I said clear off!

01:53.920 --> 01:56.773
I'm telling you, right here it says

01:56.776 --> 02:00.423
that the Lu-Qiri Overlord
mated with a human woman,

02:00.426 --> 02:02.827
and that's how there
came to be Blackbloods.

02:02.829 --> 02:04.085
Trust me, if you saw one,

02:04.088 --> 02:06.088
you'd know how impossible that is.

02:06.091 --> 02:10.570
No human would survive
such a... an encounter.

02:10.573 --> 02:12.540
I'm only telling you
what I'm reading, Talon,

02:12.543 --> 02:15.015
and unless I'm wrong about
the meaning of the word...

02:15.018 --> 02:17.073
Jekku is it? Jekku?

02:17.076 --> 02:19.310
Then mating was definitely involved.

02:19.312 --> 02:22.468
Besides, how else can
you explain your blood?

02:22.471 --> 02:24.649
Look, can you just stop
wasting your time on that stuff

02:24.651 --> 02:26.343
and find the Book of Names?

02:26.346 --> 02:29.886
The smith said we have little
time before the Dragman comes.

02:29.889 --> 02:31.923
This is it.

02:31.925 --> 02:33.906
We're here.

02:33.909 --> 02:36.265
This is Gallows Rock.

02:36.268 --> 02:39.500
Looks like a good place to be murdered.

02:39.503 --> 02:42.465
We'll wait here until sunset.

02:42.468 --> 02:44.201
That's what they said.

02:44.203 --> 02:45.703
That's what who said?

02:45.705 --> 02:47.204
The supplier.

02:47.206 --> 02:50.541
Ten to one they try and kill us.

02:50.543 --> 02:52.859
Talon, if we want to make a trade,

02:52.862 --> 02:54.929
then we have to follow the instructions.

02:54.932 --> 02:56.773
Not if you want to live.

02:56.776 --> 02:58.859
Now get up, and bring that gold.

03:16.562 --> 03:19.396
And now we wait.

03:19.399 --> 03:24.125
I don't understand why we
couldn't just wait down there.

03:32.945 --> 03:35.486
- [SIGHS]
- Are you all right?

03:35.488 --> 03:37.488
Yeah.

03:37.490 --> 03:38.960
I just think...

03:38.963 --> 03:40.653
I think I did something to my shoulder

03:40.656 --> 03:42.556
when I fought those bandits.

03:42.559 --> 03:45.007
Sorry. Sorry. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

03:54.055 --> 03:57.854
How does it feel when I go like this?

03:57.857 --> 04:00.608
[GRUNTS] I'll show you how
it feels if you do it again.

04:00.611 --> 04:02.187
Yep. Definitely dislocated.

04:02.190 --> 04:05.391
Just have to, um, loosen it up a bit.

04:13.259 --> 04:14.906
Relax,

04:14.909 --> 04:17.358
and breathe.

04:17.362 --> 04:19.462
[GROANS]

04:24.429 --> 04:26.195
Wow!

04:27.540 --> 04:29.473
Full of surprises, aren't you?

04:29.475 --> 04:31.828
There's plenty more
where that came from.

04:39.686 --> 04:42.281
Gwynn, this is my father
we're talking about,

04:42.284 --> 04:46.148
and for all the things that he is...
pig-headed, unreasonable, caustic...

04:46.151 --> 04:47.417
And traitorous!

04:47.420 --> 04:48.796
You forgot traitorous!

04:48.799 --> 04:50.507
He is currently blackmailing me.

04:50.510 --> 04:52.289
Yes, even traitorous, but the one thing

04:52.292 --> 04:56.294
that Wythers is not is a murderer.

04:56.297 --> 04:58.664
And what about your brother?

05:00.840 --> 05:03.574
Now, I hold him responsible
for Jaden's death,

05:03.576 --> 05:06.567
that's true, but that wasn't murder.

05:06.570 --> 05:08.304
Now you're just playing with words!

05:08.307 --> 05:12.343
He sent my brother to
the mine where he died!

05:12.346 --> 05:14.684
Now, I will never forgive
the bastard for that,

05:14.687 --> 05:18.539
but I am telling you, the
law is everything to Wythers.

05:18.542 --> 05:21.109
He did not murder Lilly.

05:21.112 --> 05:23.178
She is dead because of him!

05:23.181 --> 05:25.682
I know it.

05:25.685 --> 05:29.828
He found out about me and then
she disappeared the same day.

05:45.184 --> 05:48.018
Your services are no longer
required today, Captain.

05:48.020 --> 05:49.835
You're dismissed.

05:55.567 --> 05:57.906
Look at you.

05:57.909 --> 06:01.710
Little lapdog to the queen.

06:01.713 --> 06:03.515
Careful.

06:07.686 --> 06:13.122
So, um, how'd you get into brewing?

06:13.125 --> 06:15.031
The Mistress used to have a brewer.

06:15.034 --> 06:16.218
His name was Old Tunney,

06:16.221 --> 06:18.384
but he was drunk most of the time,

06:18.387 --> 06:20.387
and he didn't really
care about his craft.

06:20.390 --> 06:24.340
So, I thought if I did some
reading and taught myself,

06:24.343 --> 06:26.386
and I looked at as many
brewing books as I could,

06:26.389 --> 06:29.343
well, maybe one day I
could take his place.

06:31.238 --> 06:34.069
And make her proud.

06:34.072 --> 06:35.572
And I guess you did that.

06:35.575 --> 06:37.541
Yeah.

06:37.544 --> 06:40.514
All except the "make mother proud" part.

06:42.672 --> 06:43.928
Yeah.

06:43.931 --> 06:47.280
I, um, I wanted to talk to
you about that, actually.

06:48.915 --> 06:51.514
She's not really your mother, is she?

06:51.517 --> 06:53.784
My blood mother... Well,
she was the barmaid,

06:53.787 --> 06:57.589
but she was very young when she
gave birth to me and my twin sister.

06:57.592 --> 07:00.626
- Twin?
- Mm.

07:00.629 --> 07:02.729
She actually died doing so.

07:04.337 --> 07:06.405
I'm sorry.

07:06.408 --> 07:08.074
The Mistress, however,

07:08.077 --> 07:10.544
she thought it would be
a good idea to keep me.

07:10.547 --> 07:13.448
She thought a son would be useful,

07:13.451 --> 07:17.453
but she ended up selling my
twin sister to the slavers.

07:17.456 --> 07:21.525
She said that she couldn't
afford to keep us both.

07:21.528 --> 07:23.218
That's horrible.

07:30.574 --> 07:31.673
They're coming.

07:31.676 --> 07:33.776
[SPEAKING GREYSKIN]

07:33.779 --> 07:35.530
- Wait. Is that...
- Get down.

07:35.533 --> 07:36.665
Ow.

07:39.298 --> 07:41.699
[SPEAKING GREYSKIN]

07:41.701 --> 07:45.669
Wait. That can't be...

07:45.671 --> 07:47.358
Greyskins.

07:47.361 --> 07:50.328
Oh, my.

07:50.331 --> 07:52.198
[GROWLING]

07:53.577 --> 07:55.843
<i>[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]</i>

07:55.846 --> 07:59.483
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

08:06.039 --> 08:07.539
Wanna tell me why Greyskins

08:07.542 --> 08:09.264
would be selling colipsum to humans?

08:09.267 --> 08:10.466
It's a very good question.

08:10.469 --> 08:12.122
Whatever the reason, it must be bad.

08:12.125 --> 08:15.133
- So what do we do now?
- We stay still, keep quiet,

08:15.136 --> 08:17.310
and wait till dark to make our escape.

08:17.313 --> 08:19.585
But I can't go back
without the colipsum.

08:19.587 --> 08:21.544
Do you know what Greyskins
like to eat, Janzo?

08:21.547 --> 08:24.602
- Mm. But that's why I brought you here.
- You.

08:24.605 --> 08:26.205
You brought me here to keep you alive

08:26.208 --> 08:27.607
and that's what I'm trying to do.

08:27.610 --> 08:29.595
Talon, if I go back empty-handed,

08:29.597 --> 08:31.700
Mother will make me
wish I was dead anyways.

08:31.703 --> 08:34.145
I'm sorry, but I have to at least try.

08:34.149 --> 08:36.735
We have to make a plan at least.

08:46.981 --> 08:48.664
Send him in.

08:56.766 --> 08:59.352
Your Majesty.

08:59.355 --> 09:02.389
Look at you up there on your throne.

09:02.392 --> 09:06.864
Lilly was more than just a
handmaid to me, Mr. Wythers.

09:06.867 --> 09:09.034
She was my friend.

09:09.036 --> 09:12.130
And I intend to get to the
bottom of this awful business,

09:12.133 --> 09:15.040
not 'cause she was your
maid, but because it's my job.

09:17.149 --> 09:20.246
It was you, you son of a bitch.

09:20.248 --> 09:22.633
You murdered her!

09:22.636 --> 09:25.470
I know it!

09:25.473 --> 09:29.687
Those are very strong
words, Your Majesty,

09:29.690 --> 09:33.025
but I'm sure you have the
evidence to back 'em up.

09:33.027 --> 09:36.996
I am the queen, Mr. Wythers.

09:36.998 --> 09:39.064
I don't need evidence to take your head.

09:39.066 --> 09:41.033
Queen?

09:41.035 --> 09:43.002
Queen of what?

09:43.004 --> 09:46.492
Last I checked, General
Calkussar ruled this place,

09:46.495 --> 09:50.030
under the behest of the Prime Order,

09:50.033 --> 09:54.379
or have your abdicated your
responsibilities completely?

09:54.382 --> 09:56.949
You gonna kill me

09:56.951 --> 09:59.418
'cause your little girlie's upset?

09:59.420 --> 10:00.886
CALKUSSAR: No.

10:00.888 --> 10:02.321
I'm going to kill you

10:02.324 --> 10:04.722
because of your attempted
extortion of the queen.

10:04.725 --> 10:06.191
Yeah.

10:06.193 --> 10:08.160
I am blackmailing her,

10:08.162 --> 10:11.397
but if you don't want those letters
to go directly to the Prime Order

10:11.399 --> 10:15.267
and let Dred himself
find out truth about you,

10:15.269 --> 10:17.569
I'd let it go.

10:25.055 --> 10:27.211
Tell me again about those letters.

10:27.214 --> 10:30.474
They're in the safe
hands of a trusted friend,

10:30.477 --> 10:34.586
ready to be sent in the
event of my untimely death.

10:34.588 --> 10:37.523
Fine.

10:37.533 --> 10:40.200
Then there will be no untimely death.

10:42.578 --> 10:44.563
It'll just feel like it.

10:44.565 --> 10:46.799
What's that supposed to mean?

10:46.801 --> 10:51.031
You will be sent to the
mines to pay for your crime.

10:52.279 --> 10:56.047
I think that's rather fitting,
given your family history.

10:57.305 --> 10:59.802
Don't you?

10:59.805 --> 11:01.771
Is this your will, too?

11:01.774 --> 11:04.516
If it were up to me,
I'd cut off your head.

11:04.518 --> 11:07.219
You should consider
this an act of mercy.

11:08.689 --> 11:10.821
Your badge, sir.

11:21.571 --> 11:23.602
CALKUSSAR: Take him to the mine.

11:24.939 --> 11:26.505
Prisoner division.

11:27.808 --> 11:29.438
Lower shaft.

11:38.128 --> 11:41.262
[PRISONERS COUGH]

12:01.610 --> 12:02.810
Anything?

12:02.813 --> 12:05.065
- Overheard Raelius talking.
- And?

12:05.068 --> 12:07.903
They'll march us to the Outpost
when they have enough men.

12:07.906 --> 12:10.211
If they get us to the Outpost,

12:10.214 --> 12:11.512
it is too late.

12:11.515 --> 12:13.048
We'll be going to war.

12:13.051 --> 12:15.867
War with the Prime Order.

12:15.870 --> 12:17.870
I never signed up for that.

12:17.873 --> 12:20.525
It is now, then.

12:20.528 --> 12:25.431
Whoever pulls the black bead
will have to escape the camp

12:25.433 --> 12:27.566
and go warn the Prime Order.

12:36.492 --> 12:39.912
Swear on the Three that
no matter who draws it,

12:39.914 --> 12:41.821
we never betray each other.

12:50.193 --> 12:53.194
There's Prime Order
stationed in Hamling.

12:53.197 --> 12:56.617
You'll be leaving tonight after dark.

13:15.874 --> 13:19.176
[GROANS]

13:21.114 --> 13:24.215
[GROANS]

13:25.652 --> 13:27.552
[GROANS]

13:27.554 --> 13:29.120
Round up all of his friends

13:29.122 --> 13:31.263
and take them back to Captain Spears.

13:36.596 --> 13:39.797
[SPEAKING GREYSKIN]

13:39.799 --> 13:41.766
[GROWLS]

13:41.768 --> 13:45.336
This is gold.

13:45.338 --> 13:47.305
[SPEAKING GREYSKIN]

13:48.408 --> 13:50.104
[SPEAKING GREYSKIN]

13:50.107 --> 13:52.009
[GROWLS]

13:54.514 --> 13:58.583
[STAMMERING] I will trade you my gold

13:58.585 --> 14:01.919
for your colipsum. Mm?

14:01.921 --> 14:04.288
[SPEAKING GREYSKIN]

14:04.290 --> 14:06.818
- Mm?
- [SPEAKING GREYSKIN]

14:06.821 --> 14:12.462
This is nineteen-and-a-quarter
brick weights of pure gold.

14:12.465 --> 14:15.933
Do you use brick weights
in your system of trade?

14:15.935 --> 14:18.402
[SPEAKING GREYSKIN]

14:21.040 --> 14:23.341
[GROWLS]

14:23.343 --> 14:25.743
They don't understand, Talon.

14:25.745 --> 14:28.536
A blade to the throat means
the same in any language.

14:28.539 --> 14:30.947
It's okay. She doesn't
mean to hurt anyone.

14:30.950 --> 14:32.802
It's just a precaution, I promise.

14:32.805 --> 14:36.319
My gold for your colipsum,

14:36.322 --> 14:38.013
that's all I want.

14:40.160 --> 14:42.693
[SPEAKING GREYSKIN]

14:52.939 --> 14:54.205
[SNARLING]

15:01.693 --> 15:04.348
It's colipsum, all right,

15:04.350 --> 15:06.669
but this is way too much.

15:06.672 --> 15:09.072
We only need ten brick weights.

15:09.075 --> 15:10.922
We can't take all of this.

15:10.924 --> 15:13.024
Here. You can keep one.

15:13.026 --> 15:14.692
Shut up, Janzo.

15:14.694 --> 15:16.027
Grab the bag.

15:16.029 --> 15:18.496
[SPEAKING GREYSKIN]

15:23.701 --> 15:26.001
[GROWLS]

15:33.980 --> 15:35.416
It was way too easy.

15:35.419 --> 15:37.148
Easy?

15:37.150 --> 15:39.240
I think I just peed myself a little bit.

15:46.259 --> 15:49.794
- [KNOCKING ON DOOR]
- Come.

15:49.797 --> 15:52.565
Commander Calkussar to see you, Miss.

15:52.568 --> 15:54.298
Send him in.

15:57.203 --> 15:59.270
You may go.

16:03.209 --> 16:04.775
Ugh. The girl is worthless.

16:04.777 --> 16:06.177
Sit with me.

16:06.179 --> 16:10.248
The queen has nothing
to do but play cards?

16:10.250 --> 16:12.580
But I'm not the queen, am I?

16:12.583 --> 16:13.818
I'm locked in my tower,

16:13.820 --> 16:16.407
with no friends, no responsibilities.

16:16.410 --> 16:18.276
What is a queen without a kingdom?

16:18.279 --> 16:20.346
You shall have a kingdom soon enough.

16:20.349 --> 16:23.261
Mm.

16:23.263 --> 16:24.927
So, this new handmaid,

16:24.930 --> 16:27.146
Naya apparently is her name.

16:27.149 --> 16:28.682
She's a pitiful creature.

16:28.685 --> 16:30.854
Not a thing in her head.
She can't even play cards.

16:30.857 --> 16:33.619
Good. Gambling is
unbefitting for a queen.

16:33.622 --> 16:37.011
Octor is not gambling,
it's all about the odds.

16:37.014 --> 16:38.338
Besides, you only say that

16:38.341 --> 16:42.419
because you're completely
inept at cards, Father.

16:42.422 --> 16:43.555
Here.

16:47.256 --> 16:49.190
I hate to say this,

16:49.193 --> 16:51.760
it's probably time to
stop calling me Father.

16:56.190 --> 16:59.157
You sacrificed everything for me.

16:59.160 --> 17:03.019
You raised me and
protected me as your own.

17:03.022 --> 17:06.156
As far as I'm concerned,
you'll always be my father.

17:12.211 --> 17:15.560
Well, if we're going
to play, let's play.

17:16.683 --> 17:18.512
Who is this Naya anyway?

17:18.516 --> 17:21.354
She's the only one we've vetted
for her love of the crown.

17:21.357 --> 17:24.355
We must know we can trust
her beside the queen.

17:24.357 --> 17:26.190
Ugh. I don't like her.

17:26.192 --> 17:27.992
You won't like anyone after Lilly.

17:27.993 --> 17:30.728
- [KNOCKING ON DOOR]
- BOTH: Come.

17:33.255 --> 17:36.005
- Yes?
- A message from a Captain Garret.

17:36.008 --> 17:37.635
He requests both your presence

17:37.637 --> 17:39.203
at the gate marshal's office.

17:54.821 --> 17:55.920
[SMACKS LIPS]

17:58.991 --> 18:01.625
[LAUGHING]

18:04.617 --> 18:05.950
Ambassador!

18:05.953 --> 18:07.572
They said you were away until...

18:07.575 --> 18:10.101
We rode through the night.

18:10.103 --> 18:12.703
Is there any correspondence?

18:12.705 --> 18:15.439
Yes, yes.

18:15.441 --> 18:18.909
A bird came for you,
from Gallwood Outpost.

18:28.225 --> 18:30.058
You shall suffer seven score lashings

18:30.061 --> 18:31.727
and be relieved of command.

18:31.730 --> 18:34.638
Your wench will be put to the sword.

18:35.721 --> 18:38.995
She... She's the quartermaster's wife.

18:38.998 --> 18:41.298
Then I've done him a favor.

18:41.300 --> 18:44.168
And since you were
with another man's wife,

18:44.170 --> 18:46.395
- you shall die with her.
- But, sir...

18:46.398 --> 18:47.729
Get out.

18:47.732 --> 18:49.807
[CRYING]

18:56.616 --> 18:59.401
"Tiberion Shek and Bones dead.

18:59.404 --> 19:02.620
Blackblood stains found.

19:02.622 --> 19:04.655
Shek only checked ears of women."

19:07.326 --> 19:09.727
This means the Blackblood
survivor is a woman.

19:13.425 --> 19:16.263
And she's probably still at the Outpost.

19:19.272 --> 19:21.439
We will go there.

19:21.441 --> 19:23.374
And one way or the other,

19:23.376 --> 19:25.654
we will kill the Blackblood.

19:28.748 --> 19:30.896
Even if I have to
kill every woman there.

19:39.579 --> 19:41.946
[GROANS]

19:44.662 --> 19:46.340
- [PUNCH LANDS]
- [GROAN]

19:46.343 --> 19:48.143
What is it, Garret?

19:48.145 --> 19:50.378
Raelius caught a
deserter trying to flee,

19:50.380 --> 19:52.131
and reveal our existence
to the Prime Order.

19:52.134 --> 19:53.495
- [PUNCH LANDS]
- Then like a fool,

19:53.498 --> 19:55.077
he brought him back here.

19:55.080 --> 19:58.486
I thought that the marshal's office
would be the safest place at present...

19:58.489 --> 20:01.041
- [PUNCH LANDS]
- away from prying military eyes.

20:01.044 --> 20:03.858
- Who is this man?
- He's one of our new recruits.

20:03.861 --> 20:06.094
Are there any other
conspirators working with him?

20:06.096 --> 20:08.797
- [PUNCH LANDS]
- [GROANS]

20:08.799 --> 20:10.832
Raelius has rounded up his friends.

20:10.834 --> 20:13.634
We're trying to get that
information out of him now.

20:18.242 --> 20:21.049
Which of these other
men are working with you?

20:22.052 --> 20:23.485
You will answer me!

20:23.488 --> 20:26.119
Sergeant! You will not
strike that man again.

20:28.692 --> 20:31.533
This is how the Prime
Order treats prisoners.

20:34.658 --> 20:36.689
It won't be how we treat them.

20:39.681 --> 20:41.581
Am I clear?

20:41.584 --> 20:43.650
Yes, Your Majesty.

20:49.872 --> 20:51.338
Are there others in your conspiracy

20:51.341 --> 20:53.575
against the crown, sir?

20:58.048 --> 21:01.517
The punishment for desertion is death,

21:01.520 --> 21:03.306
unless you confess

21:03.309 --> 21:06.143
and tell me the names
of your co-conspirators.

21:08.031 --> 21:10.765
Hail to the Three.

21:16.733 --> 21:19.935
Your Majesty, a moment.

21:27.160 --> 21:28.993
He isn't working alone.

21:28.996 --> 21:31.174
His friends over there,
I would bet anything

21:31.177 --> 21:33.113
that they're as loyal
to the Covenant as he is.

21:33.116 --> 21:35.216
They were recruited to fight Greyskins,

21:35.218 --> 21:36.785
not overthrow the Prime Order.

21:36.787 --> 21:38.587
There are always going to be those

21:38.589 --> 21:40.288
that don't support our cause.

21:40.290 --> 21:43.592
Majesty, we cannot have them
mixing in with the other men.

21:43.594 --> 21:44.947
It will poison the morale...

21:44.950 --> 21:48.189
Right now, the fate of
one man is to be decided.

21:48.192 --> 21:50.293
These other men have committed no crime.

21:50.296 --> 21:51.603
Not yet, perhaps.

21:51.606 --> 21:54.734
Let me torture them.
They'll confess to any...

21:54.737 --> 21:57.033
Thank you, Sergeant,

21:57.036 --> 21:58.970
for capturing this deserter.

21:58.973 --> 22:01.073
You're dismissed, Sergeant.

22:08.351 --> 22:10.283
Conspiracy could spread.

22:10.286 --> 22:12.520
Torturing them may spread it further.

22:12.522 --> 22:14.956
What do you think the
others will say about us?

22:14.958 --> 22:19.194
Hmm? Or do you want me to
kill them all without cause?

22:19.196 --> 22:20.908
No?

22:20.911 --> 22:22.510
So, just the leader, then.

22:24.275 --> 22:26.334
Are you sure?

22:26.336 --> 22:27.822
I'm sure.

22:27.825 --> 22:30.213
We're to execute him immediately then?

22:30.216 --> 22:32.850
Yes.

22:34.840 --> 22:36.339
Very well.

22:47.755 --> 22:52.792
For his desertion of duty and
his disloyalty to his queen,

22:52.795 --> 22:55.595
I sentence this man to die.

22:58.669 --> 23:01.463
May his final thoughts be penitent.

23:06.943 --> 23:09.077
[WHISPERS] You must raise your hand.

23:16.468 --> 23:18.602
[GASPS]

23:26.596 --> 23:28.213
You will go back to the camp,

23:28.216 --> 23:29.775
and when you arrive

23:29.778 --> 23:32.645
you will tell them
exactly what you have seen.

23:32.648 --> 23:36.036
You will tell them that
unlike the Prime Order,

23:36.039 --> 23:39.107
your queen is a just queen.

23:39.109 --> 23:41.124
You will relay that
unlike the Prime Order,

23:41.127 --> 23:45.246
I do not torture and I do
not execute without cause.

23:45.248 --> 23:50.285
But I must... I must enforce our laws

23:50.287 --> 23:53.188
and I must demand loyalty.

24:09.627 --> 24:12.291
I don't like that aspect of the crown.

24:14.560 --> 24:17.061
I imagine it's...

24:17.064 --> 24:19.017
It's one of the most difficult.

24:22.025 --> 24:25.026
Look out there.

24:25.029 --> 24:26.896
What do you see?

24:28.425 --> 24:30.486
A dirty little town,

24:30.489 --> 24:33.046
forgotten at the end of the world.

24:33.049 --> 24:35.482
Yes, but it's more than that, isn't it?

24:35.485 --> 24:38.520
It's a place of promise,

24:38.523 --> 24:41.424
a last refuge of hope.

24:41.427 --> 24:44.638
Beyond these walls, countless
thousands of my people,

24:44.641 --> 24:48.610
all looking to me to somehow
bring them peace and happiness.

24:48.612 --> 24:50.166
We will.

24:50.169 --> 24:51.802
You will.

24:51.805 --> 24:56.007
If you had to choose between
saving the Realm or me...

24:59.120 --> 25:02.521
what would you choose?

25:02.524 --> 25:05.025
They're one and the same.

25:05.028 --> 25:07.962
They are not the same.

25:07.965 --> 25:11.166
You swore an oath to
the crown, to Rosmund.

25:12.987 --> 25:16.355
Now, swear that you are mine.

25:16.358 --> 25:19.611
Not for the Realm, not for the crown.

25:19.614 --> 25:21.380
For me.

25:25.057 --> 25:28.024
I am yours to command

25:28.027 --> 25:31.896
until your enemies are dead
and you sit on the throne.

25:31.899 --> 25:33.899
And after that?

25:33.902 --> 25:37.603
I've never dared to imagine after that.

25:37.606 --> 25:39.666
I have no title, no land.

25:39.669 --> 25:41.720
Don't be stupid. All of that can change

25:41.723 --> 25:44.088
with one stroke of my
quill when I become queen.

25:44.091 --> 25:46.458
When you become queen,
you will choose what's best

25:46.461 --> 25:49.328
for the peace and
prosperity of the Realm.

25:51.233 --> 25:53.158
I'll choose what I want.

26:02.658 --> 26:06.793
Is that what we're fighting
for, probably dying for?

26:08.191 --> 26:10.814
A queen who puts herself
before her people?

26:15.148 --> 26:17.431
We're fighting for freedom, Garret.

26:17.434 --> 26:20.017
That includes my freedom.

26:20.020 --> 26:23.011
To choose for myself.

26:23.014 --> 26:25.147
To be happy.

26:31.850 --> 26:34.383
[WHEEZING]

26:34.386 --> 26:36.750
[COUGHING]

26:36.753 --> 26:38.486
Silence!

26:38.488 --> 26:40.288
[GRUNTS]

26:41.458 --> 26:44.559
[GROANS]

26:55.472 --> 26:57.105
- [SQUEALING]
- [GRUNTS]

27:01.067 --> 27:03.901
- [SQUEALING]
- [GRUNTS]

27:10.234 --> 27:12.034
Trouble at the cages, sir.

27:12.037 --> 27:13.955
They've turned Plagueling and escaped.

27:23.815 --> 27:24.948
[GRUNTS]

27:33.510 --> 27:34.642
[GRUNTS]

27:36.443 --> 27:38.577
- Are you all right?
- Yeah.

27:38.580 --> 27:40.346
[GROANS]

27:47.390 --> 27:50.224
[GRUNTS]

27:50.226 --> 27:51.650
[SQUEALING]

27:51.653 --> 27:53.519
[GROANS]

28:01.972 --> 28:03.806
- You two all right?
- Aye.

28:03.809 --> 28:05.142
Good.

28:05.145 --> 28:06.912
Anyone stung?

28:08.921 --> 28:11.655
Burn the bodies.

28:11.658 --> 28:13.792
Organize a corpse patrol.

28:15.586 --> 28:17.720
Yes, sir.

28:31.597 --> 28:34.064
- [GASPS]
- Captain, you all right?

28:34.067 --> 28:35.500
Fine.

28:35.548 --> 28:37.088
Fine.

28:37.091 --> 28:40.556
I just... I need to
get back to the Outpost.

28:50.668 --> 28:52.702
He hits them, he deserves it.

28:52.704 --> 28:55.571
- JANZO: [LAUGHS] Really?
- [TALON LAUGHS]

29:15.026 --> 29:16.692
[LOUD CLANG]

29:16.694 --> 29:18.861
What are you doing?

29:18.863 --> 29:21.410
We're right by where
those two bandits were.

29:21.413 --> 29:23.866
Don't want to get stabbed in
the middle of the night, do we?

29:23.868 --> 29:26.118
They weren't bandits.
They were musicians,

29:26.121 --> 29:28.189
and one of them's going to
have to crawl to get here.

29:28.191 --> 29:29.839
Talon, my darling,

29:29.841 --> 29:32.514
where there are two there
are likely to be many.

29:32.517 --> 29:34.183
We can't be too safe, can we?

29:34.186 --> 29:36.310
You're more likely
to attract Plaguelings

29:36.313 --> 29:37.846
with the racket you're making.

29:37.848 --> 29:39.848
Now hold up your end of the bargain.

29:39.850 --> 29:41.855
Get over here and read some books.

29:54.082 --> 29:57.165
You're so slow.

29:57.167 --> 29:58.667
What are you going to do?

29:58.669 --> 29:59.894
I'm going to sleep.

29:59.897 --> 30:02.115
Shouldn't you be out here
on watch or something?

30:02.118 --> 30:04.352
Wasn't that why you built this barrier?

30:04.355 --> 30:07.389
Besides, who's gonna
be out in this weather?

30:07.392 --> 30:09.363
Now less talking, more reading.

30:13.400 --> 30:15.134
Right.

30:19.731 --> 30:22.865
[BELL RINGING]

30:36.875 --> 30:41.010
Where do you think
you're going, Marshal?

30:41.013 --> 30:45.048
That bell means it's
water break, doesn't it?

30:45.051 --> 30:47.238
You don't remember me, do ya?

30:47.241 --> 30:49.041
Not sure.

30:49.044 --> 30:50.543
Well, I remember you.

30:50.546 --> 30:52.761
We all do, don't we, boys?

30:52.764 --> 30:55.143
And hardly a man down here
has been sent down here

30:55.146 --> 30:56.855
for next to nothing.

31:00.904 --> 31:04.639
Oh, wait. Yeah, I do remember you.

31:04.642 --> 31:07.243
You're Rogan Threefingers.

31:07.246 --> 31:08.862
You stabbed the baker's boy,

31:08.865 --> 31:11.299
- didn't ya?
- That's right.

31:12.443 --> 31:15.177
- [GRUNTS]
- [GROANS]

31:36.151 --> 31:38.418
What are you looking at, ya halfwit?

31:39.752 --> 31:42.937
Ah, our newly promoted man.

31:42.940 --> 31:44.957
Marshal Higgs, is it?

31:44.960 --> 31:48.484
At your service, milady.

31:48.487 --> 31:50.521
Is this how you present yourself

31:50.524 --> 31:51.980
in an official capacity?

31:51.983 --> 31:53.793
Oh.

31:57.024 --> 32:00.025
What can I do for you, milady?

32:00.028 --> 32:02.489
Captain Spears left
the Outpost last night.

32:02.492 --> 32:04.492
Did he return?

32:04.494 --> 32:06.457
Gate log.

32:09.633 --> 32:11.503
[CLEARS THROAT]

32:14.104 --> 32:15.457
Yes, Mum.

32:15.460 --> 32:17.760
He passed through the gate and came back

32:17.763 --> 32:22.207
in to the Outpost with three
of his men at the highest moon.

32:22.210 --> 32:23.652
Well, then where is he?

32:23.655 --> 32:25.508
He hasn't checked in
with Commander Calkussar

32:25.511 --> 32:27.314
and nobody's seen him.

32:27.317 --> 32:29.699
Perhaps he's somewhere tying one on.

32:35.325 --> 32:37.089
I facilitated your advancement

32:37.092 --> 32:39.225
and I can just as easily cast you down

32:39.228 --> 32:41.028
as I did your predecessor.

32:41.031 --> 32:43.031
You?

32:43.034 --> 32:45.601
You mean your father?

32:46.632 --> 32:49.567
Yes, my father.

32:49.570 --> 32:52.704
Don't underestimate the
influence I have with him.

32:52.707 --> 32:54.574
All right.

32:54.577 --> 32:56.844
Me and Danno'll find your captain.

32:58.615 --> 33:00.793
See to it he's found.

33:03.816 --> 33:05.420
What are you standing there for?

33:05.422 --> 33:07.074
Go find him.

33:20.577 --> 33:22.810
Still breathing. Grab him.

33:58.152 --> 34:00.407
[SIGHS]

34:00.410 --> 34:02.444
Thank you.

34:02.446 --> 34:04.412
Don't thank me.

34:04.414 --> 34:06.414
You have friends in high places.

34:06.416 --> 34:08.050
[SIGHS]

34:08.053 --> 34:10.708
My son.

34:10.710 --> 34:12.643
Don't know who your son is,

34:12.647 --> 34:16.542
but Mistress paid me nicely
to keep an eye out for you.

34:18.476 --> 34:20.511
Who are you?

34:20.514 --> 34:21.980
Call me Sill.

34:21.983 --> 34:23.681
Just another miner.

34:23.685 --> 34:27.320
Just another miner who happens
to work for the Mistress?

34:27.322 --> 34:29.023
Now you're gettin' it.

34:29.025 --> 34:31.326
From down here?

34:31.329 --> 34:33.463
[LAUGHS]

34:34.984 --> 34:37.652
Once a gate marshal,
always a gate marshal.

34:41.164 --> 34:42.397
She...

34:42.400 --> 34:45.501
She has friends in low places.

34:45.504 --> 34:47.388
Oh. Oh. Oh. Oh.

34:47.391 --> 34:49.524
- [GROANS AND COUGHS]
- Hey, hey.

34:51.598 --> 34:53.222
Get some rest.

34:55.998 --> 34:59.100
Foreman and I have an understanding.

34:59.102 --> 35:01.621
Giving you 'til sunrise to recuperate.

35:01.624 --> 35:04.057
Better get some sleep while you can.

35:05.809 --> 35:09.244
I can smell fresh air.

35:09.246 --> 35:11.279
- [CHUCKLES]
- Where are we?

35:11.281 --> 35:13.308
Don't get your hopes up.

35:13.311 --> 35:15.443
You're still in the mines.

35:15.446 --> 35:18.280
Down a side shaft only
a few of us know about.

35:18.283 --> 35:20.855
Thank the Mistress for me.

35:24.540 --> 35:26.340
Talon! Whoa!

35:26.343 --> 35:28.443
Sorry. It's just me.

35:30.699 --> 35:32.253
You yelled.

35:32.256 --> 35:34.222
Yes, I found something,

35:34.225 --> 35:36.270
something interesting in the book.

35:36.273 --> 35:37.636
What?

35:37.639 --> 35:40.332
There's some kind of
mention of the Vex Rezicon.

35:40.335 --> 35:42.003
And what's that?

35:42.006 --> 35:44.384
Well, it basically translates
to the Book of Denomination.

35:44.387 --> 35:45.472
- De-what?
- Denomination.

35:45.475 --> 35:46.908
It basically means...

35:46.911 --> 35:50.379
It's like a list of
what things are called.

35:50.382 --> 35:53.550
It's a list of what things are called.

35:53.553 --> 35:56.554
The Book of Names!

35:56.557 --> 35:58.941
- You found it!
- [GIGGLES]

35:58.944 --> 36:00.597
Where?

36:00.600 --> 36:02.339
Well, that's just the thing.

36:02.342 --> 36:05.957
It doesn't quite say that
yet, but I'm still reading.

36:05.960 --> 36:08.292
Does it say anything about the Dragman?

36:10.407 --> 36:12.488
No. No, it doesn't.

36:13.632 --> 36:16.019
Then why'd you wake me up?

36:16.022 --> 36:18.663
Because you just told me to
tell you whenever I saw anything.

36:18.666 --> 36:20.666
That's all. So, that's what I did.

36:22.085 --> 36:23.878
Keep reading.

36:23.881 --> 36:25.881
Tell me about it in the morning.

36:25.884 --> 36:27.652
Okay.

36:44.587 --> 36:47.308
VOICE FROM PORTAL: <i>The Dragman comes.</i>

36:47.311 --> 36:49.519
<i>Not much time.</i>

36:49.522 --> 36:52.347
<i>The Dragman comes.</i>

37:05.682 --> 37:07.983
[GROWLS]

37:12.490 --> 37:14.523
Calkussar the Betrayer has failed

37:14.526 --> 37:18.161
to provide his latest shipments
of armor to my division,

37:18.164 --> 37:22.343
and he has failed to capture
or even report the Blackblood.

37:22.346 --> 37:25.573
I will march with 100 Covenant Guard

37:25.576 --> 37:27.950
to bring the Outpost under new command,

37:27.952 --> 37:31.386
and install someone
more loyal to the Order.

37:31.388 --> 37:36.058
And I will find and kill the Blackblood.

37:36.060 --> 37:39.128
Send it.

37:39.130 --> 37:42.459
You will recognize the
Blackblood when you see her?

37:52.009 --> 37:54.276
[CUPS CLANGING]

37:59.810 --> 38:01.550
- Talon!
- Mm!

38:01.552 --> 38:03.745
- Did you hear that?
- It's just the wind, Janzo.

38:03.748 --> 38:05.621
I think there's something out there.

38:05.623 --> 38:07.529
Go back to sleep.

38:12.496 --> 38:15.497
[SNIFFING]

38:15.499 --> 38:17.076
Can you smell that?

38:17.849 --> 38:20.235
- [GROWLS]
- Bone wolf!

38:21.617 --> 38:23.718
- [GROWLS]
- [GROANS]

38:26.327 --> 38:28.776
Talon. Talon!

38:28.779 --> 38:31.346
- [GROWLS]
- I think it's gonna eat me, Talon.

38:31.349 --> 38:33.909
Now would be the right
time to call your demon!

38:33.912 --> 38:37.155
That's it, keep talking.
Keep it focused on you.

38:37.158 --> 38:39.625
I was actually thinking of
trying the opposite approach.

38:42.826 --> 38:44.526
[GROWLS]

38:44.528 --> 38:47.095
- [GRUNTS]
- [SQUEALS]

38:48.265 --> 38:51.233
[GRUNTS AND GROANS]

38:52.402 --> 38:53.768
Talon!

38:55.573 --> 38:58.607
[GROANS]

39:01.879 --> 39:05.314
- [GROANS]
- Naughty bastard, take that!

39:05.316 --> 39:07.123
And that!

39:07.184 --> 39:08.951
- [GROWLS]
- And that!

39:20.526 --> 39:22.559
Bone wolves are scared of fire.

39:22.562 --> 39:24.018
I read it somewhere.

39:24.021 --> 39:29.271
So, this Traptak bark
burns like molten steel.

39:32.109 --> 39:33.909
You were brilliant.

39:33.911 --> 39:35.711
I should have thought of it right off,

39:35.713 --> 39:39.147
but I couldn't think of
anything else except for dying.

39:43.187 --> 39:45.220
You saved my life.

39:45.222 --> 39:48.357
Yes, I suppose I did.

39:55.199 --> 39:56.670
Sorry, mum,

39:56.673 --> 39:58.399
but we haven't found Captain Spears yet.

39:58.402 --> 40:00.105
Are you sure he returned to the Outpost?

40:00.108 --> 40:02.526
Yes. We checked with the sentries,

40:02.529 --> 40:04.755
the watch, the gatesman again.

40:04.758 --> 40:05.790
They all confirmed

40:05.793 --> 40:07.275
that he was here two nights ago,

40:07.278 --> 40:08.574
but since then no one's seen him.

40:08.576 --> 40:10.845
If Garret's missing, he's
most likely in trouble.

40:10.848 --> 40:12.452
You'll gather your men and search again,

40:12.455 --> 40:15.883
and you won't stop searching
until you've found him. Am I clear?

40:15.886 --> 40:17.912
Yes, milady.

40:31.790 --> 40:34.925
[COUGHING]

